The paper deals with consensus algorithms, which are typically studied in the Distributed Computing (cs.DC) and Distributed Systems (cs.DS) sub-categories. The use of iterative algorithms and the absence of a global parameter suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. The paper also deals with Byzantine faults, which are a common topic in the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the use of approximation techniques suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
